  "prompt": "How do you protect a tech startup idea?",
  "response": "To protect a tech startup idea, consider these strategies:\n\n1. Intellectual Property Protection\n- File a provisional or non-provisional patent\n- Register trademarks\n- Copyright software code\n- Use non-disclosure agreements (NDAs)\n\n2. Legal Strategies\n- Keep detailed documentation of idea development\n- Use confidentiality agreements with potential investors/partners\n- Consider forming a legal business entity (LLC, C-Corp)\n\n3. Cybersecurity Measures\n- Secure digital assets\n- Use encrypted communication\n- Limit access to sensitive information\n- Implement strong password protocols\n\n4. Confidentiality Practices\n- Restrict sharing detailed information\n- Be selective about who you discuss the idea with\n- Use one-way confidentiality agreements\n- Avoid public discussions before protection\n\n5. Strategic Approaches\n- Develop a minimum viable product (MVP)\n- Build a prototype quickly\n- Focus on execution, not just the idea\n- Consider first-mover advantage\n\n6. Professional Guidance\n- Consult with:\n- Intellectual property lawyers\n- Tech startup advisors\n- Patent attorneys\n\n7. Online Protection\n- Secure domain names\n- Protect social media handles\n- Use secure cloud storage\n\nRemember: Ideas alone aren't typically protected, execution matters most.",
